==English==
===Noun===
'''coon'''
#(''informal'') A [[raccoon]].
# (''slang'') A black person.
#: ''I'm about to bring out my [[ace]] boon coon T-man.''-Duo, (''On the Regular'')
'''Usage note:''' The [[w:Southern American English|American South]] [[dialect]] usually uses the term '''coon''' more than other dialects.

===Verb===
'''to coon'''
# (''slang, AAVE'') To [[steal]] from [[somebody]].
# (''slang, AAVE'') To have social time with [[friend|friends]].
